WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:01.379
Alright!

00:00:01.379 --> 00:00:04.030
Let's get the command-line tool installed on

00:00:04.030 --> 00:00:04.788
your laptop.

00:00:05.641 --> 00:00:08.681
Three steps. Open the install page, pick

00:00:08.681 --> 00:00:11.481
your operating system, then paste the command

00:00:11.481 --> 00:00:12.441
into your terminal.

00:00:13.407 --> 00:00:15.887
Head to the install page and scroll down to the quick

00:00:15.887 --> 00:00:19.007
install section. It generates the right one-liner

00:00:19.007 --> 00:00:20.527
for whatever platform you're on.

00:00:23.928 --> 00:00:26.488
Here we go. Paste the install command into

00:00:26.488 --> 00:00:29.048
your terminal and let it run. The script

00:00:29.048 --> 00:00:31.848
verifies your platform, downloads the latest stable

00:00:31.848 --> 00:00:34.888
binary, and drops it into your home directory

00:00:35.368 --> 00:00:38.488
. No system-wide install, no sudo. Watch

00:00:38.488 --> 00:00:41.128
it work. The binary is on disk

00:00:41.128 --> 00:00:43.288
and you can call it from any shell.

00:00:46.494 --> 00:00:49.054
Install done. The rdc binary

00:00:49.054 --> 00:00:49.854
is on your path.

00:00:53.277 --> 00:00:55.837
Install done. Let's confirm it. The version

00:00:55.837 --> 00:00:58.477
flag prints what just got installed, so we

00:00:58.477 --> 00:00:59.437
know it's on your path.

00:01:00.425 --> 00:01:02.185
Version printed. You're good to go.

00:01:03.124 --> 00:01:05.764
The command-line tool lives on your laptop. The

00:01:05.764 --> 00:01:08.564
server runs a separate component called renet,

00:01:09.044 --> 00:01:12.164
which the CLI provisions and drives over SSH

00:01:12.644 --> 00:01:14.644
, so you never need to log in manually.

00:01:15.627 --> 00:01:18.587
That's the install done. Next up, we'll

00:01:18.587 --> 00:01:21.307
set up your SSH key so the CLI

00:01:21.307 --> 00:01:22.427
can reach your servers.
